Frequently Asked Questions

What is Xtensio?
Xtensio is a creative collaboration platform to design living documents, work together with internal and external teams, and flexibly share your work as digital presentations, responsive web pages or exportable PDF or PNGs.
Whats a folio?
Folios are full-screen digital presentations, responsive web pages and exportable PDF or PNGs all-in-one. A folio can be anything from a brief business strategy exercise to a full-length presentation. Start with one of our templates, or create anything you need with the blank slate tool.

Your folios are live pages that you can edit and collaborate on with colleagues, clients and other key players. All of your changesfrom dragging and dropping modules, to editing graphs, to changing colors will save and sync instantly across devices. Heres more on Making a Folio.
Do I have limits on the number of templates I can try?
No. You can try all of our free templates with any of our plans. The limitations are only on your active folios.
Is my data private and secure?
Yes. All Xtensio plans include 128 bit SSL encryption and backups to ensure your data is secure. Your work belongs to you. Your folios are private unless you decide to share them or make them public. Heres more on the range of sharing options on Xtensio, from completely private to public.
Is Xtensio really free?
Yes. You will never be asked to provide credit card information for Xtensios free account.
What would I get by upgrading to a premium plan?
By upgrading to our premium plans, youll create a private and branded workspace with your own URL where you, your team members and guests can create and collaborate on multiple presentations and documents, lock branding across your deliverables with the team style guide, streamline the creation process with custom templates, unlock exports, add password protection and customize individual shared links, and view folio stats to stay updated on all of your folios. Heres more about our premium plans.
What would I use the one pager template for?
Startups can use the one-pager template to present your business idea to different people. Unlike your website, which speaks to a general audience, one-page summary allow you to succinctly convey your message to a targeted audience. This will allow you to capture interest, identify potholes in your business plan and focus your teams decision-making.
Do you have any examples I can use?
Yes! We have a couple of startup one pager examples above that you can use as a starting point for your own. If you find a style you like, use it for your inspiration. Just click on one of the examples further up on this page to save it as a folio and start editing with your own content.
How do I define my positioning statement?
A positioning statement is a one or two-sentence declaration that communicates your brands unique value to your customers in relation to your main competitors. You can find an exercise for establishing a strong positioning statement in our how-to guide.
Can I add colleagues to edit my one pager?
Yes! On the Business plan, you can invite as many people as youd like to collaborate on your one pager, ensuring your whole team is aligned. Heres more on real-time collaboration.
How do I share my one pager?
When youre ready to share your one-page summary, choose between presenting it as a full-screen digital slideshow, sending it as a responsive web link or exporting your one pager as a PDF or PNG (premium feature). All of your share options are located at the top right of your edit screen. Learn more about the different ways to share your folios in this tutorial video.
Do you have other tools for showcasing my business?
We do! There are a number of different templates, examples and resources to guide you through the process of promoting your brand. Check out our Marketing toolbox and our Business Development toolbox to find more tools and resources.

User Persona Template, Examples & How-To Guide

Every decision you make, from product features to the tone of your taglines, needs to answer to your customers.
